Paper: hep-th/9812169

Date: 1998-12-18

Title: Orbifolds of AdS(3) and fixpoints of the CFT

Authors: Klaus Behrndt

Comments: 7 pages, LaTeX; minor corrections; refs added

Journal-ref: Fortsch.Phys. 48 (2000) 15-18

The 3-d BTZ black hole represents an orbifold of $AdS_3$ gravity. The UV aswell as the IR region of the CFT is governed by a gauged SL(2, R) WZW model. Inthe UV it corresponds to a light-cone gauging (Liouville model) whereas in theIR it is a space-like gauging (2-d black hole).